If I had to guess, the outer stage uprights were assembled 0.5" closer together than the CAD specifies, perhaps due to being one spot over on a regular 0.5" hole pattern. We had a similar problem with the Thrifty elevator.

Alternately, check if your outer stage uprights are the same dimension between through the entire length. It can be hard to see small inwards bowing on very long assemblies.

We also messed up by confusing the middle and outer stage uprights (only a 1" difference), so there is plenty of opportunity here for critical but hard-to-spot errors. This is compounded if you had less experienced team members doing the final assembly. We were able to teach the finer points of being detail-oriented through these errors.

If I had to guess, the outer stage uprights were assembled 0.5" closer together than the CAD specifies, perhaps due to being one spot over on a regular 0.5" hole pattern. We had a similar problem with the Thrifty elevator.

Or your center horizontal cross pieces are 1/2" too long. Those 1/2" bearings are supposed to ride on the outside of the tube, so something is definitely up there. Better / more detailed pictures might help us figure out whatâ€™s happening here.
